WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:01:33.026 --> 00:01:34.747
Excuse me.
Manager Woo?

3
00:01:35.859 --> 00:01:36.834
Something the matter?

4
00:01:36.893 --> 00:01:38.474
Sir. take a look at this.

5
00:01:38.847 --> 00:01:42.615
A C-rank dungeon raid consisting of eight
hunters. six of whom were killed in action.

6
00:01:42.875 --> 00:01:45.914
A D-rank and an E-rank are the
only ones who made it out alive.

7
00:01:46.014 --> 00:01:48.797
I imagine they fled.
happens all the time.

8
00:01:48.923 --> 00:01:49.614
You would think.

9
00:01:49.638 --> 00:01:52.232
but they defeated the boss and
cleared the dungeon before leaving.

10
00:01:52.840 --> 00:01:53.612
Hm.

11
00:01:54.012 --> 00:01:57.126
D-rank hunter Jinho Yoo seems
to have been armed with expensive

12
00:01:57.150 --> 00:01:59.874
gear that might explain how the two
lowest ranked were able to survive.

13
00:01:59.899 --> 00:02:00.940
What's the issue then?

14
00:02:00.964 --> 00:02:03.577
You're making a report
here. not stating a problem.

15
00:02:03.602 --> 00:02:04.785
Oh. right!

16
00:02:05.124 --> 00:02:07.394
What caught my attention
is that the other hunter was

17
00:02:07.418 --> 00:02:09.908
also a survivor of that
double dungeon incident.

18
00:02:10.222 --> 00:02:11.800
It's Jinwoo Sung. sir.

19
00:02:12.227 --> 00:02:13.494
He was the E-rank?

20
00:02:16.740 --> 00:02:17.389
Hm.

21
00:02:18.180 --> 00:02:20.381
Yes. and another thing
worth noting. sir.

22
00:02:20.406 --> 00:02:23.158
is that one of the six
deceased is Dongsuk Hwang.

23
00:02:24.459 --> 00:02:27.099
The infamous Dongsoo Hwang's older brother.

24
00:02:28.479 --> 00:02:30.428
I can see why you
brought this to me.

25
00:02:32.073 --> 00:02:33.033
I'm home.

26
00:02:33.254 --> 00:02:34.508
Hey. welcome back.

27
00:02:35.601 --> 00:02:36.697
Is that fried chicken?

28
00:02:36.814 --> 00:02:39.337
What's the occasion? Something
good must have happened.

29
00:02:40.534 --> 00:02:43.388
Could be good. could be bad.
I'm not really sure yet.

30
00:02:43.940 --> 00:02:46.295
Let's just say I've got
our bills covered for now.

31
00:02:46.366 --> 00:02:47.475
Including mom's.

32
00:02:47.629 --> 00:02:50.755
Yeah. that's not weird at all coming
from a cheapskate like you.

33
00:02:52.189 --> 00:02:53.357
Oh. yeah!

34
00:02:54.744 --> 00:02:56.907
I've been meaning to ask
about how that thing went.

35
00:02:56.973 --> 00:02:57.453
Hm?

36
00:02:58.040 --> 00:02:58.822
Your raid?

37
00:02:58.899 --> 00:03:00.447
Clearly it paid well enough.

38
00:03:00.667 --> 00:03:02.669
But you didn't end up in
the hospital this time.

39
00:03:02.693 --> 00:03:04.661
so your party was
super strong. right?

40
00:03:08.730 --> 00:03:10.770
Yeah. guess so.

41
00:03:11.490 --> 00:03:13.710
I bet you beat the
bad guys easily.

42
00:03:15.296 --> 00:03:16.516
I really did.

43
00:03:17.397 --> 00:03:19.826
Everything about that
moment was easy.

44
00:03:20.570 --> 00:03:23.890
When the time came.
I didn't hesitate for a second.

45
00:03:24.539 --> 00:03:28.708
If anything. I resented them for
thinking they were even close to my league.

46
00:03:29.880 --> 00:03:32.900
The old me definitely would have
tried to find a way out of it.

47
00:03:33.394 --> 00:03:36.362
Has leveling up also
made me braver?

48
00:03:37.339 --> 00:03:39.309
Those weren't magic beasts. though.

49
00:03:39.570 --> 00:03:41.072
They were humans.

50
00:03:41.717 --> 00:03:42.559
Jinwoo?

51
00:03:43.349 --> 00:03:45.759
Hey. is everything alright
with you over there?

52
00:03:46.102 --> 00:03:49.500
Yeah. thought I might have forgotten
to grab a change. but I was wrong.

53
00:03:50.784 --> 00:03:52.817
Man. are you serious?
Is that all?

54
00:03:58.130 --> 00:03:59.409
Ah. screw it

55
00:03:59.882 --> 00:04:03.542
What matters is getting stronger so
I can stay alive and help my family.

56
00:04:03.862 --> 00:04:06.490
Whoever tries to stop
me will be just as dead.

57
00:04:07.449 --> 00:04:08.089
Hm?

58
00:04:08.850 --> 00:04:09.434
What?

59
00:04:09.654 --> 00:04:11.477
A harmful substance?

60
00:04:14.216 --> 00:04:15.271
Detoxing?

61
00:04:19.070 --> 00:04:20.792
Alright. I'm finished.

62
00:04:21.839 --> 00:04:24.585
Oh. well then if you're really
done. is it okay if I eat the rest?

63
00:04:24.716 --> 00:04:27.154
Sure. but don't cry to me
when you put on weight.

64
00:04:38.493 --> 00:04:40.152
I'm not even buzzed.

65
00:04:40.959 --> 00:04:44.452
A buff from the system must be
killing the effects of the alcohol.

66
00:04:44.532 --> 00:04:46.729
Like a status effect. maybe?

67
00:04:48.393 --> 00:04:49.193
A blessing?

68
00:04:50.180 --> 00:04:51.782
Health and longevity.

69
00:04:52.873 --> 00:04:55.639
Disables toxic and abnormal conditions.

70
00:04:55.727 --> 00:04:58.112
Improved regenerative capacity.

71
00:04:58.340 --> 00:04:59.579
That's right.

72
00:04:59.926 --> 00:05:01.803
My reward for the double dungeon.

73
00:05:02.079 --> 00:05:04.776
So much has happened since then.
I guess I never checked it out.

74
00:05:05.553 --> 00:05:08.319
Certainly explains why my
missing limbs came back.

75
00:05:09.727 --> 00:05:11.687
But there's still a lot I don't know.

76
00:05:17.427 --> 00:05:21.155
Hey. sorry to bother you. but you've got
a call from some guy named Jinho Yoo.

77
00:05:24.094 --> 00:05:25.214
Be right there.

78
00:05:25.241 --> 00:05:25.781
Huh?

79
00:05:26.328 --> 00:05:27.854
Whoa. easy on
the beer. dude.

80
00:05:27.888 --> 00:05:29.140
It's poison and I can't.

81
00:05:29.165 --> 00:05:31.035
I'm not dying
from beer. Jinah.

82
00:05:33.434 --> 00:05:36.041
When I become a doctor.
don't expect me to treat you.

83
00:05:37.260 --> 00:05:39.976
I know this is out of the blue.
so thanks for meeting me.

84
00:05:40.069 --> 00:05:41.915
I didn't think I'd
ever see you again.

85
00:05:41.940 --> 00:05:43.063
I'm glad. though.

86
00:05:43.429 --> 00:05:45.757
I'd be a dead man if it
weren't for you. boss.

87
00:05:45.980 --> 00:05:49.797
Yeah. well. giving me your share of
the essence stones helped me out. too.

88
00:05:50.517 --> 00:05:54.152
And you've kept quiet. so I
consider us pretty much square.

89
00:05:54.926 --> 00:05:58.964
Of course. I mean. why would I blab?
I know you only did that in self-defense.

90
00:05:59.340 --> 00:06:00.957
It was either them or us.

91
00:06:01.997 --> 00:06:03.846
Anyway. what's up?

92
00:06:05.599 --> 00:06:07.652
I'd really like to put together a strike
team and thought that you would......

93
00:06:07.677 --> 00:06:08.819
That's a hard pass.

94
00:06:09.812 --> 00:06:12.295
You're gonna decline
without hearing any details?

95
00:06:12.469 --> 00:06:15.515
I'm not interested in
humoring some trust fund kid.

96
00:06:15.667 --> 00:06:17.115
Just 20 raids!

97
00:06:17.567 --> 00:06:20.070
No. 19 more is all I ask!

98
00:06:20.381 --> 00:06:21.847
Oddly specific.

99
00:06:22.054 --> 00:06:23.731
What. do you want to be a guildmaster?

100
00:06:23.871 --> 00:06:26.008
Exactly. so hear me out. boss.

101
00:06:26.033 --> 00:06:27.013
I'm begging you!

102
00:06:32.585 --> 00:06:33.820
Fine. go on.

103
00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:36.385
Okay!

104
00:06:38.421 --> 00:06:42.436
I figure you know the steps to become a
guildmaster since you caught on so quickly.

105
00:06:42.461 --> 00:06:44.562
But yes. I need at
least 20 raids worth of

106
00:06:44.586 --> 00:06:47.196
experience to get my
license. and I'm 19 away.

107
00:06:47.299 --> 00:06:49.489
I haven't done any more
since the one we did.

108
00:06:50.569 --> 00:06:52.804
There's a written test. too.
but I've studied my whole life

109
00:06:52.828 --> 00:06:55.036
to inherit Yoojin Co.
so I'll ace that.

110
00:06:55.294 --> 00:06:57.777
It's just the hands-on stuff

111
00:06:59.087 --> 00:07:01.899
You're the second son of
Yoojin Construction's CEO.

112
00:07:02.956 --> 00:07:05.336
This is all related to the
company. believe it or not.

113
00:07:05.542 --> 00:07:08.702
You see. my father is in the
process of forming a guild.

114
00:07:08.929 --> 00:07:10.929
For a construction company?

115
00:07:11.056 --> 00:07:11.749
Yes

116
00:07:13.606 --> 00:07:18.315
As dangerous as dungeons are. the
treasures inside them justify the risk.

117
00:07:19.275 --> 00:07:22.637
Essence stones and Mana crystals
are only the tip of the iceberg.

118
00:07:22.683 --> 00:07:26.300
The remains of higher-ranked beasts
are used for a number of things.

119
00:07:26.325 --> 00:07:30.293
If it's found in a dungeon. chances
are it holds some monetary value.

120
00:07:30.487 --> 00:07:34.751
So. basically. you want a group of hunters
who you employ to go around clearing gates.

121
00:07:34.934 --> 00:07:37.000
Then your corporation cashes in.

122
00:07:37.135 --> 00:07:38.482
Man. you are sharp.

123
00:07:38.663 --> 00:07:40.677
Yeah. my dad wants to run
the guild like a business.

124
00:07:40.708 --> 00:07:43.425
So he'll hire an S-rank
hunter to be the leader.

125
00:07:43.449 --> 00:07:45.257
and then my brother
will be the VP.

126
00:07:45.399 --> 00:07:46.531
An S-rank?

127
00:07:46.556 --> 00:07:48.606
There are seven in
the whole country.

128
00:07:48.739 --> 00:07:49.552
Right?

129
00:07:50.152 --> 00:07:54.399
The only one not affiliated with the guild
is Byung-gyu Min. but he retired already.

130
00:07:55.220 --> 00:07:58.224
Wait. so he's gonna
poach one of them?

131
00:08:00.237 --> 00:08:01.879
Might want to
rethink that plan.

132
00:08:02.053 --> 00:08:04.314
You'll gain a leader. but
you'll also make an enemy.

133
00:08:04.339 --> 00:08:07.992
Sure. but since my brother hasn't awakened.
 he's out of the running completely.

134
00:08:08.419 --> 00:08:11.447
So you're gonna rack up enough 
experience to be qualified.

135
00:08:11.665 --> 00:08:13.187
and change your father's mind.

136
00:08:13.305 --> 00:08:14.584
Yes. that's the goal.

137
00:08:14.644 --> 00:08:16.297
So help yourself by helping me.

138
00:08:16.400 --> 00:08:18.620
You want to raid while
hiding your power. don't you?

139
00:08:18.799 --> 00:08:21.036
And I want to raid with
hunters who are lower-ranked.

140
00:08:21.103 --> 00:08:23.787
If I can succeed with an 
E-rank as opposed to an S.

141
00:08:23.811 --> 00:08:25.672
my dad will be much 
more convinced.

142
00:08:27.447 --> 00:08:29.061
Boss has to be B-rank.

143
00:08:29.507 --> 00:08:31.087
No. he's way stronger.

144
00:08:31.614 --> 00:08:33.983
Picking the wrong person
for this could get me killed.

145
00:08:34.220 --> 00:08:35.539
But if it's him...

146
00:08:39.859 --> 00:08:40.679
Take a look.

147
00:08:42.240 --> 00:08:44.641
That building was going
to be the HQ for the guild.

148
00:08:44.760 --> 00:08:47.427
It's appraised for 30 billion
and will keep going up.

149
00:08:48.347 --> 00:08:51.176
19 successful raids
from now. it's all yours.

150
00:08:51.666 --> 00:08:55.063
19 C-rank raids
for 30 billion.

151
00:08:55.180 --> 00:08:57.750
There was a time I would've
jumped at an offer like that.

152
00:08:57.857 --> 00:09:03.292
But now. I'm the sole person who
can level up. and that changes things.

153
00:09:03.372 --> 00:09:07.768
If I keep increasing my stats.
I could even reach S-rank.

154
00:09:08.020 --> 00:09:10.501
Or maybe go beyond that.

155
00:09:11.447 --> 00:09:14.620
30 billion is honestly chump
change with that in mind.

156
00:09:14.702 --> 00:09:17.468
And I'm still not sure how
leveling up will affect me.

157
00:09:17.575 --> 00:09:20.384
So I really don't like the idea
of working with somebody else.

158
00:09:20.472 --> 00:09:21.812
It's just too risky.

159
00:09:24.100 --> 00:09:24.940
I'm sorry!

160
00:09:29.319 --> 00:09:30.439
Boss. hang on!

161
00:09:31.666 --> 00:09:33.080
Work with me on this.

162
00:09:33.133 --> 00:09:35.913
And I swear to you. I'll take
your secret to the grave!

163
00:09:49.899 --> 00:09:52.223
I want details on
the two survivors.

164
00:09:52.605 --> 00:09:54.207
Get me their info ASAP.

165
00:09:57.763 --> 00:09:58.841
Mr. Hwang?

166
00:09:59.694 --> 00:10:02.189
Forgive the intrusion. but
I have those documents.

167
00:10:05.106 --> 00:10:06.846
My brother was murdered.

168
00:10:09.960 --> 00:10:11.410
Do you have any evidence
that your brother.....

169
00:10:11.410 --> 00:10:12.294
Intel.

170
00:10:14.107 --> 00:10:15.789
Right. here you are sir.

171
00:10:16.523 --> 00:10:20.549
Laura. what are the consequences
of killing someone abroad?

172
00:10:20.997 --> 00:10:22.249
Are you serious?

173
00:10:28.072 --> 00:10:30.406
If you do so in a country
with an extradition

174
00:10:30.430 --> 00:10:32.403
treaty for all
hunter-related crimes.

175
00:10:32.567 --> 00:10:34.309
You would have to stand trial there.

176
00:10:34.926 --> 00:10:36.586
But if they don't
have such a treaty.

177
00:10:37.052 --> 00:10:39.149
You'd be sent home
for prosecution.

178
00:10:40.506 --> 00:10:41.566
And in that case?

179
00:10:41.839 --> 00:10:45.524
You may be able to negotiate for a
reduced sentence if you're tried here.

180
00:10:46.859 --> 00:10:48.099
Clear my schedule.

181
00:10:48.913 --> 00:10:52.966
Sudden changes will disrupt the guild
and business will grind to a halt. sir.

182
00:10:53.370 --> 00:10:54.740
How far am I booked out?

183
00:10:55.220 --> 00:10:56.630
For the immediate future.

184
00:10:57.560 --> 00:10:58.780
Then it can wait.

185
00:10:59.050 --> 00:11:00.309
But pencil it in.

186
00:11:00.516 --> 00:11:01.809
Of course. Mr. Hwang.

187
00:11:02.170 --> 00:11:03.523
Thank you for understanding.

188
00:11:04.526 --> 00:11:07.003
D-rank hunter Jinho Yoo.

189
00:11:07.486 --> 00:11:09.846
E-rank hunter Jinwoo Sung.

190
00:11:12.982 --> 00:11:16.956
You bastards better stay alive
till I have time to deal with you.

191
00:11:21.463 --> 00:11:24.403
You've never exercised
much before. so why now?

192
00:11:24.637 --> 00:11:26.566
Well. all I ever do is study.

193
00:11:26.619 --> 00:11:28.153
It's like super unhealthy.

194
00:11:28.219 --> 00:11:31.473
Right. so much worse than eating
a whole mountain of chicken.

195
00:11:38.460 --> 00:11:41.602
Hey. if we had 30 billion.
what would you do with it?

196
00:11:41.813 --> 00:11:43.222
Where is this coming from?

197
00:11:43.553 --> 00:11:44.582
Just curious.

198
00:11:45.376 --> 00:11:47.311
A chunk would go to mom's bills.

199
00:11:47.638 --> 00:11:49.059
And another for college.

200
00:11:49.113 --> 00:11:50.193
Then what?

201
00:11:51.980 --> 00:11:53.021
Save it?

202
00:11:53.327 --> 00:11:54.364
I don't know?

203
00:11:54.580 --> 00:11:56.259
It's too unrealistic?

204
00:11:57.160 --> 00:11:58.399
Yeah. right?

205
00:11:59.387 --> 00:12:01.313
Don't try to keep up with me. okay?

206
00:12:01.540 --> 00:12:03.034
What the heck. JinWoo?

207
00:12:07.050 --> 00:12:09.554
Geez. even E-rank hunters are extra.

208
00:12:15.982 --> 00:12:17.284
Hold on. go back.

209
00:12:18.219 --> 00:12:19.624
11 out of 10.

210
00:12:20.839 --> 00:12:23.862
So it tracks how much I run
even after I hit the goal.

211
00:12:29.056 --> 00:12:30.154
All right. then.

212
00:12:30.510 --> 00:12:32.207
Let's see how
far I can go.

213
00:12:36.667 --> 00:12:38.127
All right. finally.

214
00:12:38.349 --> 00:12:41.075
I was starting to think I
would never catch up to you.

215
00:12:41.484 --> 00:12:43.181
I'm gonna run a little more.

216
00:12:43.206 --> 00:12:44.278
More?

217
00:12:50.423 --> 00:12:52.485
Maxed out at 20 kilometers.

218
00:12:52.617 --> 00:12:53.845
Let's check the others.

219
00:13:01.509 --> 00:13:05.330
The daily quest became a secret quest
because I doubled all of the reps?

220
00:13:06.306 --> 00:13:07.030
Yes.

221
00:13:07.470 --> 00:13:10.006
Oh. a choice of
random loot boxes.

222
00:13:11.279 --> 00:13:13.259
Well. I'm doing the
blessed one. easy.

223
00:13:29.390 --> 00:13:30.776
Another key?

224
00:13:33.190 --> 00:13:34.956
The Demon's Castle.

225
00:13:35.036 --> 00:13:36.650
S-rank?
What?

226
00:13:45.650 --> 00:13:47.719
There's a magical cure-all in there.

227
00:13:48.650 --> 00:13:50.510
The Elixir of Life.

228
00:13:58.980 --> 00:14:00.760
Seems too good to be true.

229
00:14:01.382 --> 00:14:04.282
But if this Elixir really
cures any illness.

230
00:14:04.582 --> 00:14:06.144
My mind's made up.

231
00:14:06.786 --> 00:14:07.707
I'm going.

232
00:14:16.444 --> 00:14:19.813
The acquisition difficulty probably
matches the dungeon's level.

233
00:14:19.869 --> 00:14:21.969
Which means this one's S-rank.

234
00:14:22.556 --> 00:14:26.664
Whatever's in here will be on the same
level as the Jeju Island dungeon break.

235
00:14:26.823 --> 00:14:29.756
The one even S-rank
hunters couldn't contain.

236
00:14:38.748 --> 00:14:42.001
Do I even have a chance
against threats of that level?

237
00:14:50.024 --> 00:14:52.353
I'd be lying if I said
I wasn't scared.

238
00:14:52.673 --> 00:14:54.766
But the second it
gets too intense.

239
00:14:55.045 --> 00:14:58.498
I'll use the teleportation stone I
saved from the instance dungeon.

240
00:15:05.906 --> 00:15:07.839
I won't give in to fear.

241
00:15:07.899 --> 00:15:09.993
I can't get stronger that way.

242
00:15:10.056 --> 00:15:13.496
I'll fight. I'll level up.
and take what's mine.

243
00:15:15.202 --> 00:15:17.963
I refuse to die in
a place like this.

244
00:15:39.829 --> 00:15:41.593
I've hardly damaged it.

245
00:15:41.649 --> 00:15:44.236
And that's with the buff
of my wolf assassin title.

246
00:15:50.740 --> 00:15:52.322
No dice. huh?

247
00:16:23.906 --> 00:16:24.906
A warning!

248
00:16:25.146 --> 00:16:27.499
That attack sapped
half of my health.

249
00:16:35.113 --> 00:16:36.915
It doubled its stats?

250
00:16:40.889 --> 00:16:41.769
Too fast.

251
00:16:46.284 --> 00:16:47.803
No. no. no!

252
00:16:49.264 --> 00:16:50.458
Only one choice.

253
00:16:50.511 --> 00:16:52.059
More recovery. now!

254
00:16:57.292 --> 00:16:58.574
Yes. that worked!

255
00:17:43.376 --> 00:17:45.110
No warnings won't stop.

256
00:17:45.857 --> 00:17:49.312
The system is doing everything
it can to ensure I don't die.

257
00:17:49.633 --> 00:17:51.172
Because I'm the player.

258
00:17:51.886 --> 00:17:55.880
Don't have to be a genius to tell this
is far from a normal reawakening.

259
00:17:57.034 --> 00:18:00.213
That rage status will go
away in three minutes.

260
00:18:00.654 --> 00:18:02.747
Too risky to test my luck.

261
00:18:04.619 --> 00:18:06.029
Might be time to...

262
00:18:20.352 --> 00:18:22.752
Is it even possible to survive this?

263
00:18:24.112 --> 00:18:26.147
A few more hits and I'm done for

264
00:18:26.213 --> 00:18:28.553
But there's gotta be a way.

265
00:18:29.632 --> 00:18:31.798
That's right. I have a store.

266
00:18:34.566 --> 00:18:36.125
It's in my price range.

267
00:18:36.432 --> 00:18:37.665
I'll take three.

268
00:18:43.687 --> 00:18:45.934
One just heals a hundred HP.

269
00:18:46.280 --> 00:18:47.507
Not enough.

270
00:18:49.686 --> 00:18:50.714
Poison?

271
00:18:50.920 --> 00:18:53.014
Huh? Whoa. easy
on the beer. dude.

272
00:18:53.074 --> 00:18:53.966
It's poison in a can't..

273
00:18:53.991 --> 00:18:55.560
I'm not dying
from beer. Jinah.

274
00:18:57.452 --> 00:18:58.812
I have to try.

275
00:19:16.558 --> 00:19:17.553
Here we go.

276
00:19:28.562 --> 00:19:29.365
Not yet.

277
00:19:29.956 --> 00:19:31.596
I'm still in this.

278
00:19:37.247 --> 00:19:39.027
The rage effect wore off!

279
00:21:28.504 --> 00:21:29.991
Let's see what I dropped.

280
00:21:30.779 --> 00:21:32.077
I should've figured.

281
00:21:32.436 --> 00:21:36.206
And the last key is... I bet it's for
the gate Cerberus was guarding.

282
00:21:36.812 --> 00:21:37.592
What the?

283
00:21:44.039 --> 00:21:45.477
It's for the Elixir.

284
00:21:45.559 --> 00:21:46.314
No way!

285
00:21:50.943 --> 00:21:53.583
That fight helped
me gauge my limits.

286
00:21:53.900 --> 00:21:57.216
I know if I go in that castle. I'll die.

287
00:21:57.450 --> 00:21:58.449
So....

288
00:21:59.223 --> 00:22:01.276
I'll get stronger
and come back.

289
00:22:02.322 --> 00:22:03.365
Count on it.

290
00:22:04.305 --> 00:23:04.298
